parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS accumulator pump can cause a sudden loss of power brakes, leading to accidents or near-misses, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The ABS and brake lights illuminate on the dashboard
accompanied by an audible alarm or buzzing noise; the brake pedal goes to the floor with minimal or no braking effect; the vehicle may vibrate while braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Severe corrosion of the vehicle's frame can compromise the structural integrity of the vehicle, making it unsafe to drive and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire failure can lead to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities. Unstable tires can also cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and decreased vehicle performance.
